result.execSummary:
The defendant Candace Lanea Tjomsland was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Fine of $379.00 plus DNA surcharge of $200.00 for a total due of $579.00 -   Pay obligation within 90 days or apply to the Clerk of Court for a payment plan within 90 days and pay the $15.00 payment plan fee.

judgments.dispoDesc: Court finds defendant guilty of amended charge fine of $579.00 to set up a payment plan or given 90 days to pay.

records.addlTxt: 10:13 AM back on the record.  Court questions the defendant as to the plea questionnaire.  Defendant entered plea of guilty.  State moved to delete the domestic enhancer.  Court grants motion.  State $579.00 fine requested.  Court finds defendant guilty of amended charge fine of $579.00 to set up a payment plan or given 90 days to pay.

Defendant Candace Lanea Tjomsland in court.  Bruce Robert Poquette appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Defendant advised of rights/penalties, acknowledges receipt of complaint, waives reading of complaint.  DEF states she will represent herself waives right to attorney.  DEF enters a Guilty Plea.  Scheduling conference scheduled for August 4, 2015 at 10:00 am.

Defendent Candace Lanea Tjomsland in custody via video.  John Yackel appeared for the State.   DEF satisfied with video.  PC found by court.    SISB $500

Statutory Minimum Domestic Abuse Bail Conditions
As a condition of my release from custody in this matter, I agree that I will not engage in any threats or acts of domestic abuse against the victim " ALEX TJOMSLAND " or any other person.
I understand that "domestic abuse" means:
Intentional infliction of physical pain, injury or illness.
Intentional impairment of physical condition. 
First, second or third degree sexual assault.  
A physical act that may cause the other person reason to fear imminent engagement in the conduct described above, including but not limited to the intentional destruction of physical property.
